so you’re free to relax.

270
00:15:41,375 --> 00:15:44,678
There isn’t anyone else around.
You don’t have to act

271
00:15:44,745 --> 00:15:47,715
like good little kids
who don’t know anything.

272
00:15:47,781 --> 00:15:49,516
Right now, we’re the caretaker

273
00:15:49,583 --> 00:15:51,318
and the children
meant to be food.

274
00:15:51,385 --> 00:15:52,519
( Both gasp )

275
00:15:52,586 --> 00:15:55,522
Isabella: However, I must admit,

276
00:15:55,589 --> 00:16:00,761
I love every one of the children
i’ve raised. I do, truly,

277
00:16:00,828 --> 00:16:03,664
as if you all
were my own children.

278
00:16:03,730 --> 00:16:07,667
That’s why I came out here
to ask that you just give up.

279
00:16:07,734 --> 00:16:09,636
Emma: You want us to...

280
00:16:09,703 --> 00:16:10,637
Norman: Give up?

281
00:16:12,739 --> 00:16:14,674
( Both gasp )

282
00:16:14,741 --> 00:16:17,043
Isabella: Give up resisting.

283
00:16:19,546 --> 00:16:22,416
i love you all
and don’t want you to suffer,

284
00:16:22,482 --> 00:16:23,583
and I especially don’t want

285
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:25,385
to be the cause
of your suffering.

286
00:16:25,452 --> 00:16:27,688
This life is happy, isn’t it?

287
00:16:27,754 --> 00:16:30,023
You get to live in a warm house

288
00:16:30,090 --> 00:16:32,125
filled with delicious food
and love.

289
00:16:32,192 --> 00:16:34,695
if you can stay
oblivious to the truth,

290
00:16:34,761 --> 00:16:37,597
then you are able to die
feeling satisfied.

291
00:16:41,201 --> 00:16:43,804
So how does that sound
like anything but paradise?

292
00:16:43,871 --> 00:16:45,473
( Emma gasps )

293
00:16:45,539 --> 00:16:47,341
That’s what you think this is?

294
00:16:47,407 --> 00:16:49,609
are you saying
that this "happy life"

295
00:16:49,676 --> 00:16:51,411
was worth what conny
went through?

296
00:16:51,478 --> 00:16:53,714
Isabella: Death happens
in an instant.

297
00:16:53,780 --> 00:16:55,649
Until the moment she died,

298
00:16:55,716 --> 00:16:58,719
conny experienced a rich life
full of smiles and laughter.

299
00:16:58,785 --> 00:17:01,755
( Emma gasps ) What’s the point
if it’s all just fake?!

300
00:17:01,822 --> 00:17:05,025
I’m going to live freely,
even if I suffer for it!

301
00:17:05,092 --> 00:17:07,628
Then i’ll decide happiness
for myself!

302
00:17:07,694 --> 00:17:09,763
( Shudders )

303
00:17:09,830 --> 00:17:11,999
Norman: Stop.

304
00:17:12,065 --> 00:17:13,466
( Grunts )

305
00:17:13,534 --> 00:17:14,568
Emma: Norman...

306
00:17:14,635 --> 00:17:16,637
isabella:
Escaping is impossible,

307
00:17:16,703 --> 00:17:18,672
and it’s dangerous outside.

308
00:17:18,739 --> 00:17:20,641
You don’t really want
to go out there.

309
00:17:23,277 --> 00:17:26,580
Now, why don’t we all go back
to living happily together,

310
00:17:26,647 --> 00:17:28,382
like none of this happened?

311
00:17:28,448 --> 00:17:31,685
My greatest wish is for the five
of you to live joyous lives

312
00:17:31,752 --> 00:17:33,687
until your time
eventually runs out.

313
00:17:33,754 --> 00:17:36,557
Norman: Five? Not three?

314
00:17:39,293 --> 00:17:40,694
( Both grunt )

315
00:17:43,330 --> 00:17:45,032
( Both gasp )

316
00:17:45,098 --> 00:17:46,566
( Both sigh )

317
00:17:51,805 --> 00:17:53,640
Norman: Fine. You win, mom.

318
00:17:53,707 --> 00:17:55,809
( Isabella chuckles )

319
00:17:55,876 --> 00:17:57,678
Norman: I’ll stop
being a good kid.

320
00:17:57,744 --> 00:17:58,678
Isabella: Huh?

321
00:18:00,214 --> 00:18:02,049
Isabella: Go, Norman!

322
00:18:08,088 --> 00:18:09,056
( Chuckles )

323
00:18:09,122 --> 00:18:10,557
( Crack )

324
00:18:13,327 --> 00:18:14,662
( Norman gasps )

325
00:18:14,728 --> 00:18:16,663
( Emma gasping )

326
00:18:18,131 --> 00:18:20,066
( Wailing )

327
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:21,468
( All gasp )

328
00:18:21,535 --> 00:18:22,469
Ray: Emma.

329
00:18:22,536 --> 00:18:25,472
( Emma sobbing )

330
00:18:25,539 --> 00:18:27,441
( Isabella chuckles )

331
00:18:31,545 --> 00:18:34,048
Shh. Shh.

332
00:18:34,114 --> 00:18:35,582
You’re going to be okay.

333
00:18:35,649 --> 00:18:38,585
It doesn’t hurt. Don’t cry.

334
00:18:38,652 --> 00:18:41,121
Aw, poor thing.

335
00:18:41,188 --> 00:18:43,190
My adorable Emma.

336
00:18:43,257 --> 00:18:46,327
this is why
I told you to give up.

337
00:18:46,393 --> 00:18:49,263
But i’m glad you hugged me
for the first time in a while.

338
00:18:49,329 --> 00:18:50,397
( Chuckles )

339
00:18:50,464 --> 00:18:53,167
And you realized it
quickly, Norman.

340
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:54,167
I’m impressed.

341
00:18:56,537 --> 00:19:00,107
Yes, i’ll control all of you
until the very end,

342
00:19:00,174 --> 00:19:03,344
because you’re different
than most of the other children.

343
00:19:03,410 --> 00:19:08,415
You’re special food that only
a special one is able to eat,

344
00:19:08,482 --> 00:19:12,453
the highest quality of children
i’ve ever raised.

345
00:19:12,519 --> 00:19:14,454
( Emma winces )

346
00:19:14,521 --> 00:19:15,756
♪

347
00:19:15,822 --> 00:19:17,457
Norman: So, then...

348
00:19:17,524 --> 00:19:21,194
Isabella: That’s why
I have to protect you all,

349
00:19:21,261 --> 00:19:22,462
no matter the cost.

350
00:19:22,529 --> 00:19:24,564
I was forced to do this,

351
00:19:24,631 --> 00:19:26,766
because it was clear
you weren’t going to give up.

352
00:19:26,834 --> 00:19:30,271
( Emma gasping )

353
00:19:30,337 --> 00:19:34,241
( Wails )

354
00:19:37,144 --> 00:19:39,046
( Children laughing )

355
00:19:39,112 --> 00:19:40,680
Naila: Mom!

356
00:19:45,552 --> 00:19:47,654
Oh, no! What happened to Emma?

357
00:19:47,721 --> 00:19:50,190
Mark: Did she get hurt?

358
00:19:50,257 --> 00:19:52,192
( Chorus vocalizing )

359
00:19:54,261 --> 00:19:55,596
Boy: Look!

360
00:19:55,662 --> 00:19:56,596
( Boy 2 gasps )

361
00:19:56,663 --> 00:19:58,665
( Children gasp )

362
00:20:00,234 --> 00:20:01,168
Phil: Huh?

363
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:04,805
( Emma gasps )

364
00:20:04,872 --> 00:20:06,807
Isabella: You won’t be able
to move for a while,

365
00:20:06,874 --> 00:20:09,510
which means i’ll have
no worries for tomorrow.

366
00:20:09,576 --> 00:20:11,378
Ray: Tomorrow?

367
00:20:11,445 --> 00:20:13,113
Isabella: Yes. That’s right.

368
00:20:13,180 --> 00:20:15,582
you can stay
and celebrate, Emma.

369
00:20:15,649 --> 00:20:17,117
( Norman gasps )

370
00:20:17,184 --> 00:20:20,220
isabella: There was
a notice from headquarters,

371
00:20:20,287 --> 00:20:22,122
so, congrats, Norman.

372
00:20:22,189 --> 00:20:24,124
The time for you
to be shipped has come.

373
00:20:24,191 --> 00:20:26,126
( All gasp )

374
00:20:26,193 --> 00:20:27,795
( Norman shuddering )

375
00:20:27,861 --> 00:20:29,763
♪

376
00:20:36,603 --> 00:20:38,405
♪

377
00:20:38,672 --> 00:21:06,934
( Singing in Japanese )

